  m_Name: Readme
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: com.fuzzphyte.utility.editor::FuzzPhyte.Utility.Editor.FPReadmeAsset
  icon: {fileID: 2800000, guid: 0378ca7329b7827468040c7cb9c0ab30, type: 3}
  title: FuzzPhyte Package
  subtitle: Package documentation and setup notes.
  version: 0.9.5
  overview: "FP_Utility is designed and built to be a simple set of base classes
    to be used in almost all future FuzzPhyte packages. \nThere is an element of
    Scriptable Object and an element of just simple input/output functions as well
    as some core scripts timed to timers etc. \nThere are a lot of static functions
    to help with file management and Unity Editor management. \nPlease see the FP_UtilityData
    class as well as the FP_Utility_Editor class for a lot of these functions/enums/structs
    etc."
  sections:
  - heading: FP Header
    body: "FP Header is an editor-only hierarchy organization tool for Unity scenes.
      \nIt lets you create disabled, all-caps GameObjects that act like visual section
      headers in the standard Unity Hierarchy without forcing the grouped objects
      into a parent-child transform relationship. \nThis is useful when you want
      the readability and collapse behavior of folders, but you do not want to change
      transform inheritance or scene structure.\r\n\r\nA header is treated as valid
      when the GameObject name is all caps, the object is inactive, and it has no
      children. \nObjects that appear after that header in the same sibling scope
      are treated as part of the section until the next valid header is found."
    links:
    - label: Source code for FP_HHeader
      url: https://github.com/JShull/FP_Utility/blob/main/Editor/FP_HHeader.cs
  - heading: FP Scene Asset Tool
    body: "FP Scene Asset Tool is an editor window that scans the active scene and
      builds a reference list of the external assets used by that scene. \nIt is
      intended to help you audit scene dependencies such as:\nmaterials, meshes,
      textures, audio clips, prefab assets, animation assets, ScriptableObjects,
      fonts, and other referenced content. \nThis helps you can spot misplaced project
      references, redundant assets, or content coming from the wrong part of the
      project.\r\n\r\nThe tool deduplicates assets by path, groups them by detected
      type, tracks which scene GameObjects reference each asset, and marks package
      or built-in dependencies as non-selectable. \nYou can focus on project content
      you actually control.\n\nThere are other options for Bulk Texture Import and
      Bulk Audio Import - if you wanted to select these type of assets in a scene
      and force them to a lower/higher quality you can much easier than traditional
      Unity."
    links:
    - label: Source code for FPSceneAssetLister
      url: https://github.com/JShull/FP_Utility/blob/main/Editor/FPSceneAssetLister.cs
